Note:
Rust Parser - Builds Abstract Syntax Tree from Rust tokens

This file implements a recursive descent parser for the Rust programming language.
Parses Rust 2021 edition syntax including ownership, borrowing, traits, pattern
matching, async/await, macros, and all Rust-specific language features.

AST Node Types:
- RUST_PROGRAM: Root node containing all items
- RUST_STRUCT: Struct definition
- RUST_ENUM: Enum definition
- RUST_TRAIT: Trait definition
- RUST_IMPL: Implementation block
- RUST_FUNCTION: Function definition
- RUST_MOD: Module definition
- RUST_USE: Use declaration
- RUST_TYPE_ALIAS: Type alias
- RUST_CONST: Constant definition
- RUST_STATIC: Static variable
- RUST_MACRO: Macro definition
- RUST_PATTERN: Pattern matching constructs
- RUST_LIFETIME: Lifetime parameters
- RUST_GENERIC: Generic type parameters

Dependencies:
- rust_lexer.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/rust/rust_lexer.runa" as Lexer
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List

